Every time I visited Subko, I’d catch myself staring at the Hartigae House, wondering what it must feel like to actually live there—to soak in the charm of old Bandra, to slow down, and just be in that nostalgic pocket of the city.

Well… I finally did it. Thanks to @jadestayindia 
And let me tell you—it was so worth it. 🤍

From the vintage aesthetics to having cafés like Mokai, Matchabar, and of course Subko just a walk away, everything about this stay felt warm, intentional, and incredibly wholesome.

Highly, highly recommend.

STOREYYY TIME⬇️⬇️

It was our last day, and we wanted to end the trip on a relaxing note — so obviously, we booked a traditional Thai massage. The place was perfect — calm rooms, cozy lighting, and those soothing waterfall sounds playing in the background. We were so ready to transcend into spa-girl heaven.

And then… the massage started.

Within the first two minutes, our masseuses started talking — and never stopped. We don’t know what they were discussing, but we definitely caught the words “India” and “Modi” mid-elbow-in-our-back.

As two certified people pleasers, we couldn’t bring ourselves to say anything. So we just lay there, spiritually weeping, hoping they’d wrap it up soon.

The best part? We both came out of our separate massage beds, made eye contact, and immediately realized we had the exact same thought running through our heads the whole time 😂

Meanwhile here are some reasons Why Sri Lanka Should Be on Your Radar as a Solo Female Traveler 🇱🇰✨

🌊 Safe & Welcoming Vibes – Locals are warm, helpful, and respectful — especially in tourist hubs like Ella, Galle, and Mirissa.

🏝️ Perfect Mix of Chill + Adventure – Surf, snorkel, hike or just sip coconut water by the beach. You choose the pace.

Scenic & Budget-Friendly Trains – The iconic Kandy to Ella route is not just safe — it’s soul food on rails.

🛏️ Gorgeous Stays for Every Budget – Think ocean-view hostels, jungle cabins, and boutique Airbnbs that are Insta-worthy and affordable.

Wellness & Solo-Friendly Cafés – From yoga retreats to work-friendly cafés, it’s easy to feel at home even while solo.

📸 Underrated, So Less Crowded – It’s like Bali’s calmer cousin — with just the right blend of culture, coastline, and calm.

I’m not saying drop everything and hand in that leave letter right now… but if you can — then just go!

Honestly, the destination is always secondary. What matters most is the intention you set when you leave.

For my sister and me, it was all about stepping into a journey of realizing that we are enough.

And that’s exactly what it turned out to be — a raw, beautiful lesson in trusting ourselves, making our own decisions, and standing on our own feet without depending on anyone else.

Every choice we made was ours, and we owned it.

Absolutely no regrets.

(SriLanka budget-travelling women-travelling solo-travelling, travelling , beaches ]

#Womenfriendlytravel #srilanka #travelling

Is it just me or even you feel these things while coming back from the vacation? 
-
Still glowing from the memories, replaying sunsets, laughter, and slow mornings, but there’s a quiet ache knowing it’s all behind you now.

Your heart feels full – for the people you met, the food you tasted, the version of you that came alive on the trip.

As you wait to board, you catch yourself already planning the next adventure, because once you’ve felt that freedom, it’s hard to let it go.
